@startuml partnerships-sequence-apply-offer
title Partnerships: Apply to a Job Offer

actor Student
participant "Frontend\n(Angular)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(Spring Boot)" as API
participant "Auth Service\n(JWT)" as AUTH
participant "Matching Service" as ML
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

Student -> FE: Browse job offers
FE -> API: GET /api/job-offers
API -> DB: SELECT job_offers\nWHERE status = OPEN
DB --> API: Offer list
API --> FE: 200 OK (offers)
FE --> Student: Display offer cards

Student -> FE: Click on an offer
FE -> API: GET /api/job-offers/{id}
API -> DB: SELECT job_offer, company
DB --> API: Offer details + company info
API --> FE: 200 OK (offer details)
FE --> Student: Display offer detail page\nwith "Apply" button

Student -> FE: Click "Apply"\nand fill application form
FE --> Student: Display application form\n(motivation, skills, documents)

Student -> FE: Submit application
FE -> API: POST /api/applications\n{offerId, motivation, skills, cvUrl}
API -> AUTH: Validate JWT token
AUTH --> API: Token valid (studentId)

API -> DB: CHECK no existing application\nFROM same student FOR same offer
DB --> API: No duplicate found

API -> ML: calculateScore(student, offer)
ML -> DB: SELECT student profile,\nskills, past projects
DB --> ML: Student data
ML -> ML: Extract features\nand compute similarity
ML --> API: matchingScore = 0.82

API -> DB: INSERT application\nSET status = PENDING,\nmatchingScore = 0.82
DB --> API: Application created

API -> DB: INSERT notification\n(for recruiter)
API --> FE: 201 Created (applicationId)
FE --> Student: Application submitted\nsuccessfully with confirmation
@enduml
